iency ","Failure to follow the advice above may lead to loss of motorcycle control which could result in serious injury or death.","The ABS ECM is an integral part of the ABS modulator.","Do not remove the ECM from the ABS modulator.","If a new ECM is required, repair is by replacement of the ABS modulator and ECM as an assembly only.","To prevent paint damage, do not spill brake fluid onto any area of the bodywork.","Spilled brake fluid will damage paintwork.","Front Brake Caliper","Remove the fixings from one of the front calipers and slide the brake caliper off the brake disc.","Reflector assembly","Brake caliper fixings","Brake caliper","Use a suitable flat metal plate approximately 2 mm thick and 30 to 50 mm wide (for example a gasket scraper) between the brake pads. Pump the front brake lever slowly until the plate is held by the brake pads. Do not allow the pistons to fall out.","Pull the front brake lever towards the handlebar until a small amount of pressure is felt. Cable tie the brake lever to this position.","Brake lever","Cable tie","Rear Brake Caliper","Remove the fixing and remove the rear wheel speed sensor and bracket and position to one side, noting the routing for installation.","Rear wheel speed sensor","Bracket","Fixing","Clips","Wire guide","Remove the rear wheel see ","Rear Wheel - Removal","Note the position of the rear brake caliper for installation.","Detach the brake caliper from its carrier assembly.","Caliper carrier","Swinging arm lug","Caliper carrier groove","Use a suitable a flat metal plate approximately 2 mm thick and 30 to 50 mm wide (for example a gasket scraper) between the brake pads. Pump the rear brake pedal until the plate is held by the brake pads.","ABS Hydraulic Modulator/ECM","Disconnect the electrical connector from the ABS modulator.","Remove the union bolts and carefully disconnect the four brake lines from the ABS modulator, collecting any brake fluid. Discard the sealing washers.","Remove and discard the three fixings that attach the ABS modulator and bracket to the frame.","Collect the three flanged washers.","ABS Modulator bracket fixings","ABS modulator electrical connector","Brake line unions","ABS Modulator bracket","ABS modulator","Remove and discard the two fixings and remove the ABS modulator from the bracket.","If required, remove the anti-rotation moulding from the ABS modulator.","ABS Modulator","Anti-rotation moulding fixing","Anti-rotation moulding","ABS modulator bracket","Fixings"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType05","createdAt":"2024-04-18T13:07:52.461Z","updatedAt":"2024-04-18T13:07:52.461Z","__v":0}